<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 9:08PM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF NORTHWESTERN MORTON
AND SOUTHWESTERN MERCER COUNTIES THROUGH 945 PM CDT...
At 908 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located 7 miles north of
Hebron, or 20 miles southwest of Beulah, moving southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Morton
and southwestern Mercer Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
